Conclusions
- Home prices are likley capped at $500,001
- There is a strong correlation between the number of total rooms, bedrooms, population, and number of households per district
- There is a large amount of expensive houses near the bay area of California relative to other areas
- There is a decent positive correlation between median income and median house value
- There is little correlation between the total rooms and median house value in each district
